<br>
So here's the question. What is the easiest method in terms of items to create and costs involved to get from 21 in smithing to roughly 185?<br>
<br>
Also, what is the easiest method of getting to 178 tailoring from 158?<br>
<br>
I'm asking such because I want to try and be as sure of the velium gear's creation as possible. Currently my JC is definitely high enough to do the trivial combines. The thing I'm worried about other then smithing is that I'd fail the combines on the velious hound furs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=carlothecurious>Carlo the Curious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/02 4:20 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Shawl Tradeskills...</span><hr size=1> Take a look at EQ traders ( <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com">www.eqtraders.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ) for guides on raising skill.<br>
<br>
I got my smithing up before they changed all the trivials, so I'm not sure what the best way is now, but for tailoring the most efficient method would probably be to make studded or reinforced acrylia, or possibly othmir depending on whether you feel like killing the cute otters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Also, buying geerlock devices is considerably cheaper than actually raising your skill the additional 5 points or so they give you - did my combines at 165 tailoring and 185 smithing with geerlocks for both, and only failed one fur combine.<br>
<br>
--<br>
Carlo Curiosus, 61 Sorceror, Morell-Thule<br>
