<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern">Nameless Server</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khalidah>Khalidah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/02 1:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Shawl Tradeskills...</span><hr size=1> Your Tailoring is fine where it is.  With a Geerlock sewing contraption and 158 skill in tailoring I successfully made 8 out of 10 soft fur padding combinations.  The cost of buying or the time necessary to obtain a few more velium hounds fur is far cheaper than trying to raise your tailoring another 20 points!  Also, the soft fur padding is tradeable so you can have a high level tailor do the combines if you are that worried it.<br>
<br>
Smithing is almost as bad as tailoring is now to raise.  If you did not take advantage of banded armor before it was nerfed you are in for a long haul.  Just make banded armor till it goes trival around 115-120.  Then the fun starts.  To progress further you will need to do ornate chain next.  This requires HQ rings which your have to either hunt (extremely rare) or buy from the merchants who stock a limited supply.  Plus you can fail the ring attempt!<br>
<br>
Once that goes trivial you will need to do fine steel plate which requires leather padding.  Leather padding = LQ pelt + spiderling silk thread (2 Spiderling silks combined).  Good luck on this.  People are now asking like 5-10p per spiderling silk.  Considering you will need 20-40 stacks of this stuff your costs go up.  You also have to get LQ pelts which if you do not hunt add even more costs.  Last you need to make MQ folded sheets of metal which you make from MQ blocks of ore which cost 17p.  Oh did i mention you can fail the leather padding attempts and folded sheet attempts?  Ha ha thanks VI!<br>
<br>
I eventually gave up on raising smithing when i did 27 fine steel plate combines to go from 164 skill to 165 at 270int!  I just could not hunt any more silks or pelts.  So I attempted the royal velium armor at 165 skill.  I only failed the legs once so I made 7 out of 8 attempts.  Yahooo!<br>
<br>
My recommendation would be to max smithing on ornate chain, buy a geerlock hammer and attempt your royal velium armor then.  You will have to eat a few failures but I think it will be quicker and cheaper than trying to raise smithing.<br>
<br>
Good Luck<br>
<br>
Khalidah Arihant<br>
